Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine light pink-buff. Circular stamp with Helios bust symbol. Greek inscription.
Production date: 124 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Name Teisamenos. Trimmed. Three examples in the Benaki collection, Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, including ABC 0217.15, are from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1141)
